name: Alexandr Grichshenko
headline: Business Analyst and Project Manager at Tinkoff Bank
creator: False
bio:
Diligent Business Analyst and Project Manager with 2+ years of experience in Software Development process. I help companies transform various business requirements for their desired IT system into actionable tasks for the development team, create comprehensive project documentation leading to a successfull deployment of the system.

Technical skills & tools: Python, Click-Up, Confluence, Figma, Miro, CPLEX, Gurobi

Some examples of my work include:
- Oversaw the completion of tasks assigned to a team of 8 developers, cutting the project's completion time by 15% compared to earlier predictions.
- Acted as a customer support specialist, designing tasks to improve the product according to the user feedback leading to the increase in customer satisfaction of 30%.
- Analysed relevant improvement suggestions from the stakeholders at the latter stages of the projects, which led to better user experience.

I get excited about developing IT systems for a wide range of business needs, delving deeper into new spheres. For instance, I have worked with developing a web application for educational programs and a mobile application for animal farming. I am looking forward to applying my expertice to something new and gaining knowledge.

Give me a shout at alexgrichshenko1@gmail.com or here on LinkedIn!

Currently immersed in a dynamic learning environment, I am eagerly exploring the realms of Computer Science, seeking opportunities to apply my knowledge and skills to real-world challenges. With a passion for emerging technologies and a penchant for problem-solving, I am driven to push the boundaries of what's possible in the digital age. 🌐

🔧 Project Highlights:
Having embarked on several successful small-scale projects, I have honed my abilities to transform ideas into tangible solutions. These projects have not only deepened my technical proficiency but have also provided me with invaluable experiences in collaborating with diverse teams and translating concepts into action. 💡

🚀 Future-Forward Mindset:
I am determined to continuously evolve and adapt to the ever-evolving tech landscape. Whether it's AI, blockchain, cybersecurity, or software development, I am excited to embrace new challenges and contribute my unique perspective to the field. 💬

🤝 Let's Connect:

headline: Senior .Net Software Engineer
creator: False
bio:
Commenced my professional journey in the banking sector, where I adeptly pivoted from frontend to backend development, showcasing versatility and a strong technical acumen. Motivated by a commitment to personal and professional growth, I pursued a master's degree, immersing myself in a comprehensive exploration of various aspects of software development.

During this educational journey, I actively engaged in hands-on experiences across the entire software development lifecycle, further honing my skills. Subsequently, I ventured into a new professional realm, joining a company in a distinctly different industrial context. This experience broadened my perspective and allowed me to apply my expertise to varied challenges.

Fueled by a desire to contribute meaningfully and leverage my accumulated knowledge, I made the strategic decision to return to my initial banking company. Currently, I hold a pivotal role as a successful software engineer, where I am entrusted with the responsibility of overseeing one of the main financial services in Kazakhstan. This role not only underscores my technical proficiency but also highlights my capacity to navigate and excel in the dynamic landscape of financial technology.

name: Artur Smirnov
headline: ML Engineer
creator: False
bio:
I have been working in the DS field since 2021. Received a higher technical education at the university, which provided significant knowledge in the field of mathematical analysis and statistics. The thesis had a separate chapter, "predicting well production using ML methods."

I combine my work with self-education (literature, articles) and pet projects. I am currently developing my project, which uses LLM models. The project involves a personal tutor for interviews and various exams. In the industry, I try to read new articles more often, upgrade my ML knowledge in different directions and in strict formalization. (Ranking, Recommendation Systems, Time Series, Causal ml).

I would like to attend meetings and participate in competitions more often in the future.
I've been working on Notion all my life and projects.

name: Ruslan Aiginin
headline: Senior iOS Engineer at RE Partners
creator: False
bio:
I love building great apps for the Apple ecosystem!

My approach is always keeping in mind how the projects I am working on will benefit both the organisation and the users, and aiming to achieve the best possible combination of business value, user experience and technical quality.

I have over 7 years of experience working on 15 diverse projects in the fitness, fintech, enterprise, shopping, transportation and other industries, with contributions ranging from implementing new features, to developing whole apps from scratch all the way through to AppStore release, and supporting them afterwards.

I have discovered my passion for computers and software engineering early in my childhood and have been following this path ever since. I have received my Master's degree in Software Engineering from Carnegie Mellon University in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania, one of the top CS schools in the world.

name: Taimuraz T.
headline: Bringing dating back offline @ Breeze
creator: False
school_2: Orta Doğu Teknik Üniversitesi / Middle East Technical University
bio:
I'm a highly motivated Back End Engineer with a Degree in Computer Science from Innopolis University. My academic background equipped me with a strong foundation in Software Engineering.

Currently, I serve as a Back End Engineer at Avito, the world's top classified website. In this role, I am dedicated to crafting efficient micro service solutions, primarily based on Golang. My core aim is to focus on acceleration of business growth, while delivering products with great customer experience.

Throughout my career, I've embraced diverse challenges. I spearheaded the creation of a back end system for an aircraft engine repair management system, optimizing processes to achieve a remarkable 70% increase in efficiency. I also played a significant role in launching one of my client's largest marketing company. My experience extends to Go, Python, cloud configuration, Docker, Kubernetes, CI/CD setup and more.

I am deeply passionate about continuous learning and thrive when solving complex technical challenges. Clean architecture is at the core of my approach to building scalable and maintainable solutions.

I value being an integral part of a team, leveraging my diverse experiences to contribute meaningfully. With a history of taking on responsibilities to solve complex problems from the ground up, I make sure to involve team members and foster collaboration with other teams, ensuring collective success.

I'm committed to personal and professional growth, ready to expand my skill set to address the needs of both the team and the business. I believe adaptability is key to serving the greater goals of the team and organization.
